   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Start Fund Niger Wash</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following attacks in June 2016, which lead to the displacement of about new 40,000 IDPs in the Diffa region, CARE provided support to most vulnerable IDPs (18,000 beneficiaries targeted) in the WASH and Protection sectors. In specific, CARE conducted three types of activities intended to provide assistance to the new IDPs: (i) Provision of dignity kits to women in procreative age, (ii) provision of potable water to people including the host population through the construction of two boreholes, (iii) sensitization sessions and mass awareness campaigns for protection against GBV and for water hygiene and sanitation promotion.</narrative>
  </description>
